===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|釆|田|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}}. Original meaning is unclear. 

''{{w|Shuowen}}'' instead interprets it as a pictogram of an animal's footprint; original form of {{och-l|蹯}}.

Tadashi Takada (高田忠周): a pictogram of some seeds on the palm of an open hand, which conveys the concept of "spreading"; original form of {{och-l|播}}.

Neither ''Shuowen'' nor Tadashi Takada interpret the bottom component as representing a field.

===Etymology===
; “to do in turns; turn; time”
: Iterative of {{och-l|反|to turn; to return|id=1}} by aspiration of the initial ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).
; “anime series”
: {{bf|zh|新番}}.

